<div class="entry-content primary-content-column columns small-12 medium-8">
<p><span class="wf_caption" style="display: block; max-width: 640px; width: 100%;"><noscript><img src="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/legacy/images/images_2018_03/2018_0323chomsky.jpg" alt="Noam Chomsky. (Photo: Jeanbaptisteparis)" width="640" style="width: 100%; margin: auto;"></noscript><img src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%203%202'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Noam Chomsky. (Photo: Jeanbaptisteparis)" width="640" style="width: 100%; margin: auto;" data-src="https://truthout.org/wp-content/uploads/legacy/images/images_2018_03/2018_0323chomsky.jpg" loading="lazy"><span style="text-align: left; margin-top: 3px; display: block;">Noam Chomsky. (Photo: <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/jeanbaptisteparis/4295851585/in/photolist-7xBn1D-64qbTH-r6dJW2-s7jJWw-9wPeWh-aRMouc-7Rnixa-aBhQaQ-cyix3N-5ySUa-qDoZXq-c9YyzQ-WU1rHV-9wPmCN-9wLhaZ-9A5VQ-9wLgLg-bBqZGr-6o56Mf-YPSDAS-bBqZ7K-31yMx-7WkAyC-9A5UX-aurdsy-9R1r37-9A59H-31yLD-9A4AE-9R1vhf-7xFbDJ-31yE5-9A5TF-soJx9b-9A5Su-31yKh-93Ngfv-aiegJj-9dvh-9A4Cs-31yEL-aZk2vi-5LmwAx-bHM9BF-fNYBp-ZDDSJt-c2mMrL-WGc9BM-bow5EU-6A3hTd">Jeanbaptisteparis</a>)</span></span></p>
<div class="well well-small"><a href="https://truthout.org/support-us/#top" style=" line-height: 1.4em;">Did you know? Truthout is a nonprofit publication and the vast majority of our budget comes from reader donations. It&rsquo;s easy to support our work &mdash; click here to get started. </a></div>
<p>We recently interviewed Noam Chomsky, Institute Professor Emeritus at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and Laureate Professor in the Department of Linguistics at the University of Arizona. He shares his thoughts with the Institute for New Economic Thinking on foreign policy, dissent in the Internet age, public education, corporate predation, who&rsquo;s really messing with American elections, climate change, and more. </p>
<p><strong>Lynn Parramore: You&rsquo;ve been looking at politics and international relations for quite a long time. Over the decades, what are the continuities in these areas that stand out in your view?</strong></p><div class="truth-post-content-high  inline-callout-container" id="truth-255792"><aside class=" callout inline-callout callout--subscribe callout--dark" id="truth-255395">
<h2>Uncompromised, uncompromising news</h2>
<p>Get reliable, independent news and commentary delivered to your inbox every day.</p>
